<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5224881>
    dc:description "Figure 1. Pycnogonum coninsulum sp. nov., male holotype. A, trunk and proboscis, dorsal, with most coxae and entire left second leg; B, trunk, lateral (ventral profile and oviger diagrammatic, obscured by legs); C, oviger; D, third right leg with detail of split spine. Scale line51 mm for A and B, 0.13 mm for C, 0.3 mm for D." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5224881/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

